{"descriptions":[{"id":1256,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThis verb, which means \u0026ldquo;to want,\u0026rdquo; requires the main verb to be in the present-future.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eIt appears only as a modal verb (and not as a main verb), and may be combined with the following auxiliaries. It functions in a similar way to the verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eདགོས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;need.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ein the present: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་ཡོད་\u003c/span\u003e (egophoric), \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་འདུག་\u003c/span\u003e, or \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་ཡོད་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ein the past: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་བྱུང་\u003c/span\u003e (egophoric), \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་བྱུང་སོང་\u003c/span\u003e, or \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་བྱུང་བ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ein the future: \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་ཀྱི་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eThe perfective past auxiliaries \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eསོང་\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཔ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e, and \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eབཞག་\u003c/span\u003e may not directly follow the verb \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་\u003c/span\u003e. The following constructions are thus wrong: *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་སོང་\u003c/span\u003e *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་པ་རེད་\u003c/span\u003e *\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eའདོད་བཞག་\u003c/span\u003e. These example sentences are correct:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eང་གངས་ཏི་སེར་འགྲོ་འདོད་ཡོད།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;I want to go to Kailash.\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཁྱེད་རང་ཚོ་བོད་ལ་ཕེབས་འདོད་ཡོད་པས།\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Would you like to go to Tibet?\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:15:21 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}